		<span id="comment-100053582-content"><p>John,<br />
I&#39;ve been brainstorming on this topic a lot recently too. I don&#39;t have any magic solutions for you, but I did enjoy reading your article.</p>

<p>You might want to take a look at this article on my blog. It&#39;s about OSS business models:<br />
Open Source Needs More Innovation<br />
<a href="http://blog.davestechshop.net/archive/2006/08/14/OpenSourceNeedsMoreInnovation.aspx" rel="nofollow">http://blog.davestechshop.net/archive/2006/08/14/OpenSourceNeedsMoreInnovation.aspx</a></p>

<p>And this is one about Microsoft&#39;s responsibility to the open source community (which MS is not fulfilling very well in my opinion):<br />
<a href="http://blog.davestechshop.net/archive/2006/09/19/MicrosoftHasGreaterResponsibility.aspx" rel="nofollow">http://blog.davestechshop.net/archive/2006/09/19/MicrosoftHasGreaterResponsibility.aspx</a></p></span>
	</div>
	<p class="comment-footer">
		Posted by:
		<a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="http://blog.davestechshop.net/archive/2006/09/19/MicrosoftHasGreaterResponsibility.aspx" href="http://blog.davestechshop.net/archive/2006/09/19/MicrosoftHasGreaterResponsibility.aspx">Dave</a> |
		<a href="http://www.iunknown.com/2006/07/open-source-the.html?cid=100053582#comment-6a00d834fc885d53ef00e5502afe7e8834">September 19, 2006 at 06:50 PM</a>
	</p>
</div>

		</div>
        
